Extra Credit. 5 Potential Risks
1. If you are making an api call and the api is changed by the creator or changed to be paid, then the project will break.
    Severity: 4/10 
    Mitigation strategy: Check the api documentation frequently to catch any changes before they become a problem.
2. If group members aren't careful with our commits, the codebase could break.
    Severity: 3/10
    Mitigation strategy: use branches effectively to keep commits organized.
3. SQL and Javascript injections
    Severity: 8/10
    Mitigation strategy: use best practice when reading in user input.
4. Maintaining user privacy 
    Severity: 5/10
    Mitigation strategy: secure database and don't store unnecessary user data.
5. If the SQL database is organized poorly then the database would be slow at best and give incorrect data retrieval at worst.
    Sevarity: 3/10-10/10
    Mitigation strategy: Use separate tables for important pieces of infomation in order to make queries simpler and avoid loss of data risks.